                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Armor of the Zealot, a cleric self buff, is 8 per tick mana regen.
<br />

<br />
The shaman focus line does not stack with either of these though.  Nine used to, but does not any longer.
<br />

<br />
So, if a shaman and a druid are available, then the best mana regen for a cleric would be Focus and Nine.  If a druid is not available, then the best would be Armor of the Zealot.   Request Infusion of Spirit from a shaman (level 49) or beastlord (level 61) if available for extra hit points.
<br />

<br />
Armor of the Zealot
<br />
1:  Increase Max Hitpoints by 450 
<br />
2:  Increase AC by 36 
<br />
3:  Increase HP when cast by 450 
<br />
4:  Increase Mana by 8 per tick 
<br />
Infusion of Spirit
<br />
4:  Increase STR by 50 
<br />
5:  Increase DEX by 55 
<br />
6:  Increase STA by 45 
<br />

<br />
Blessing of the Nine
<br />
1:  Increase AC by 32 
<br />
2:  Increase Max Hitpoints by 618 
<br />
3:  Increase HP when cast by 618 
<br />
4:  Increase Mana by 8 per tick 
<br />
Focus of the Seven
<br />
1:  Increase Max Hitpoints by 544 
<br />
2:  Increase HP when cast by 544 
<br />
4:  Increase STR by 75 
<br />
5:  Increase DEX by 70</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
